      • setStepParams

        public FtcServoActuator.Parameters setStepParams(double maxStepRate,
                                                 double minPos,
                                                 double maxPos)
        This method sets Step Mode parameters of the servo actuator. Step Mode allows a servo to be speed controlled.
        Parameters:
        maxStepRate - specifies the maximum step rate in physical unit per second.
        minPos - specifies the minimum position limit of the servo actuator.
        maxPos - specifies the maximum position limit of the servo actuator.
        Returns:
        this parameter object.

      • setRetractParams

        public FtcServoActuator.Parameters setRetractParams(double retractPos,
                                                    double retractTime)
        This method sets the retract parameters of the servo actuator.
        Parameters:
        retractPos - specifies the retract position in physical unit
        retractTime - specifies the time in seconds required to retract from a full extend position.
        Returns:
        this parameter object.

      • setExtendParams

        public FtcServoActuator.Parameters setExtendParams(double extendPos,
                                                   double extendTime)
        This method sets the extend parameters of the servo actuator.
        Parameters:
        extendPos - specifies the extend position in physical unit
        extendTime - specifies the time in seconds required to extend from a full retract position.
        Returns:
        this parameter object.
